The market is further segmented by applications, with catalysts playing a vital role in industries such as petrochemicals, chemicals, environmental, and refining. Petrochemical catalysts are crucial for transforming raw materials into valuable products like plastics and synthetic fibers, while catalysts in the chemical sector facilitate essential reactions for chemical production. Environmental catalysts are instrumental in mitigating emissions from industrial activities, contributing to environmental sustainability. Refining catalysts are essential in the conversion of crude oil into usable fuels and other refined products, supporting the energy sector's operations.

